{
  "texts": [
    "The overall trend of the experimental data is well described by the model calculations.",
    "The light blue dashed line is the result calculated from the thermal model at chemical freeze-out ( T ch = 157 MeV at 200 GeV) for cen- tral Au+Au collisions, which overestimates the experimental data by more than a factor of two at dN ch ∕d ∼ 600 which could be due to the effects of hadronic rescattering during hadronic expansion.",
    "The black dot-dashed line is a fit to the data based on the coalescence model.",
    "The lower panel of Fig. 24 shows that most of the measurements are within a significance of 2 from the coalescence baseline, except for the enhancements observed for the yield ratios from the 0-10% most central Au+Au collisions at 19.6 GeV and 27 GeV with a significance of 2.3 and 3.4, respectively.",
    "Notably, in the net-proton higher moments and charged particle intermittency measurements, non-monotonic behaviors are observed around a collision energy of √ s NN = 20 GeV."
  ]
}